@aklapper I simply need to go to different folders to read messages for different purposes. There can be a lot of reasons. For example, a new message is coming to a folder, and I can quickly go to it. (Using space often leads me to some spam or trash folders.) Another example: Let's say you are a manager of a few teams. You would wanna switch your view when different team members come to you.

Of course, it's not as frequent as going to next/previous message, but IMO it is already frequent enough such that dedicated acceleration keys are helpful. Even if it's not, there is no harm doing this.

Your suggestion of keys have a serious drawback: You don't know how many times of `F6` you need to press, but something like `/mail/mail-next` for folders makes life a lot easier.

