Given that more than 80% of the processing time is involved in the propagate_labels function (which builds and processes a graph with the watershed-transform op), splitting the operation for a meta op is useless.

So, I have tried what follows:

- I added gegl_operation_progress to the watershed-transform operation
- I modified the [propagate_labels](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gegl/blob/master/operations/common/waterpixels.c#L271) function to use a GeglProcessor on the write node (instead of calling gegl_node_process), retrieving the progress value with gegl_processor_work and re-emit it:

```
processor = gegl_node_new_processor (write, NULL);

while (gegl_processor_work (processor, &progress))
  gegl_operation_progress (operation, progress, "");

g_object_unref (processor);
```

Unfortunately, It does not work as I expected: in Gimp (2.10), the progress indicator appears and stays at 0% as long as the filter is processing.

Any suggestions ?
